children.value: Entities define the schema of the subgraph, and represent the data that can be queried. Within each entity are sets of fields that store useful information related to the entity. Below is a list of the available entities within the Kwikswap Subgraph, and descriptions for the available fields.
To see an interactive sandbox of all entities see the
Each entity is defined with a value type, which will always be a base AssemblyScript type, or a custom type provided by The Graph's custom TypeScript library. For more information on value types see

The Kwikswap Factory entity is responsible for storing aggregate information across all Kwikswap pairs. It can be used to view stats about total liquidity, volume, amount of pairs and more. There is only one KwikswapFactory entity in the subgraph.
amount of pairs created by the Kwikswap factory
all time USD volume across all pairs (USD is derived)
all time volume in ETH across all pairs (ETH is derived)
total liquidity across all pairs stored as a derived USD amount
total liquidity across all pairs stored as a derived ETH amount
all time amount of transactions across all pairs

Information about a pair. Includes references to each token within the pair, volume information, liquidity information, and more. The pair entity mirrors the pair smart contract, and also contains aggregated information about use.
reference to token0 as stored in pair contract
reference to token1 as stored in pair contract
total supply of liquidity token distributed to LPs
total liquidity in pair stored as an amount of ETH
total liquidity amount in pair stored as an amount of USD
total liquidity with only tracked amount (see tracked amounts)
amount of token0 swapped on this pair
amount of token1 swapped on this pair
total amount swapped all time in this pair stored in USD (only tracked if USD liquidity is above minimum threshold)
total amount swapped all time in this pair stored in USD, no minimum liquidity threshold
all time amount of transactions on this pair
array of liquidity providers, used as a reference to LP entities
Stores aggregated information for a specific token across all pairs that token is included in.
amount of token traded all time across all pairs
amount of token in USD traded all time across pairs (only for tokens with liquidity above minimum threshold)
amount of token in USD traded all time across pairs (no minimum liquidity threshold)
amount of transactions all time in pairs including token
total amount of token provided as liquidity across all pairs

This entity is used to store data about a user's liquidity position. This information, along with
information from the pair itself can be used to provide position sizes, token deposits, and more.
user address and pair address concatenated with a dash
reference to the pair liquidity is being provided on
amount of LP tokens minted for this position

Transaction entities are created for each Ethereum transaction that contains an interaction within Kwikswap contracts. This subgraph tracks Mint, Burn, and Swap events on the Kwikswap core contracts. Each transaction contains 3 arrays, and at least one of these arrays has a length of 1.
array of Mint events within the transaction, 0 or greater
array of Burn events within transaction, 0 or greater
array of Swap events within transaction, 0 or greater

A user entity is created for any address that provides liquidity to a pool on Kwikswap. This entity
can be used to track open positions for users. LiquidyPosition entities can be referenced to get
specific data about each position.
array of all liquidity positions user has open

Burn entities are created for every emitted Burn event on the Kwikswap core contracts. The Burn entity stores key data about the event like token amounts, who burned LP tokens, who received tokens, and more. This entity can be used to track liquidity removals on pairs.
Transaction hash plus index in the transaction burn array
reference to the transaction Burn was included in
timestamp of Burn, used to sort recent liquidity removals
address that initiated the liquidity removal
index in the transaction event was emitted
derived USD value of token0 amount plus token1 amount
address of fee recipient (if fee is on)
amount of tokens sent to fee recipient (if fee is on)

Mint entities are created for every emitted Mint event on the Kwikswap core contracts. The Mint entity stores key data about the event like token amounts, who sent the transaction, who received the liquidity, and more. This entity can be used to track liquidity provisions on pairs.
Transaction hash plus index in the transaction mint array
reference to the transaction Mint was included in
timestamp of Mint, used to sort recent liquidity provisions
address that initiated the liquidity provision
index in the transaction event was emitted
derived USD value of token0 amount plus token1 amount
address of fee recipient (if fee is on)
amount of liquidity sent to fee recipient (if fee is on)

The Bundle is used as a global store of derived ETH price in USD. Because there is
no guaranteed common base token across pairs, a global reference of USD price is useful
for deriving other USD values. The Bundle entity stores an updated weighted average of ETH<->Stablecoin pair prices. This provides a strong estimate for the USD price of ETH that can
be used in other places in the subgraph.
derived price of ETH in USD based on stablecoin pairs

Swap entities are created for each token swap within a pair. The Swap entity can be used to get things like swap size (in tokens and USD), sender, recipient and more. See the Swap overview page
for more information on amounts.
transaction hash plus index in Transaction swap array
reference to transaction swap was included in
timestamp of swap, used for sorted lookups
derived amount of tokens sold in USD
Tracks data across all pairs aggregated into a daily bucket.
unix timestamp for start of day / 86400 giving a unique day index
unix timestamp for start of day
total volume across all pairs on this day, stored as a derived amount of ETH
total volume across all pairs on this day, stored as a derived amount of USD
all time volume across all pairs in ETH up to and including this day
total liquidity across all pairs in ETH up to and including this day
all time volume across all pairs in USD up to and including this day
total liquidity across all pairs in USD up to and including this day
reference used to store most liquid tokens, used for historical liquidity charts
tokens with most liquidity in Kwikswap
number of transactions throughout this day
Tracks pair data across each day.
pair contract address and day id (day start timestamp in unix / 86400) concatenated with a dash
unix timestamp for start of day
reserve of token0 (updated during each transaction on pair)
reserve of token1 (updated during each transaction on pair)
reserve of token0 plus token1 stored as a derived USD amount
total amount of token0 swapped throughout day
total amount of token1 swapped throughout day
total volume within pair throughout day
amount of transactions on pair throughout day
The subgraph tracks aggregated information grouped by days to provide insights to daily activity on Kwikswap. While

can be used for direct comparison against values in the past, it is much more expensive to query grouped data. For this reason the subgraph tracks information grouped in daily buckets, using timestamps provided by contract events. These entities can be used to query things like total volume on a given day, price of a token on a given day, etc.
For each DayData type, a new entity is created each day.
Tracks token data aggregated across all pairs that include token.
token address and day id (day start timestamp in unix / 86400) concatenated with a dash
unix timestamp for start of day
amount of token swapped across all pairs throughout day
amount of token swapped across all pairs throughout day stored as a derived amount of ETH
amount of token swapped across all pairs throughout day stored as a derived amount of USD
amount of transactions with this token across all pairs
token amount of token deposited across all pairs
token amount of token deposited across all pairs stored as amount of ETH
token amount of token deposited across all pairs stored as amount of USD
price of token in derived USD
amount of token deposited in pair with highest token liquidity - used only as a reference for storing most liquid pairs for this token
pairs with most liquidity for this token
